# SnapsExecutionWebView E2E variant

`app/lib/snaps/SnapsExecutionWebView.tsx` has a companion file `app/lib/snaps/SnapsExecutionWebView.e2e.tsx` that Metro loads instead during E2E builds (controlled by `resolveRequest` in `metro.config.js`).

## Key points

- The `.e2e.tsx` variant adds fetch/XHR/WebSocket proxy injection for E2E test mocking. It must export the same public API (`createWebView`, `removeWebView`, `SnapsExecutionWebView`).
- Any change to the component logic, props, lifecycle, or exported API in the base `.tsx` **must be mirrored** in the `.e2e.tsx` variant, or E2E tests will break.
- The base `.tsx` must remain completely free of E2E/test code — no imports from `util/test/utils`, no proxy injection, no `Platform` import for proxy purposes.
- Do NOT create stub files or intermediate proxy modules. The E2E code is self-contained in the `.e2e.tsx` file.
